To conclude, the relationship with food in Lockwood & Co is incredibly healthy, loving, & meaningful!

 It's treated w/ such a healthy attitude & displays so much depth in the characters; sometimes it's the little gestures that mean the most!
#SaveLockwoodandCo #HauntedWatchParty
@Godsgirljune SAAMMEEE i think of it constantly #SaveLockwoodandCo #HauntedWatchParty

It's what they do. Lockwood, Lucy and George look after each other. They make tea for each other. They ensure the others have eaten. It's their small way of showing their love for their family.

#SaveLockwoodandCo #HauntedWatchParty

He's so shaken by the attack on his brother that he's dazed, exhausted, still in shock. He's bleary and can't remember where they keep the teabags, though they're in the same place as always. 
So Lucy takes charge and makes the tea for him.
#SaveLockwoodandCo #HauntedWatchParty

In TEG, the morning George comes home after being in hospital, Lockwood seeks comfort in Lucy by hugging her- which we know means he truly WAS distraught.

The second thing he does is make tea. Or, attempt to. 
#SaveLockwoodandCo #HauntedWatchParty

Tea is another example of food being a love language in the books and show! It's a huge part of their relationships with each other.

It's clearly a comfort.

In the show, we see Lockwood making tea for Lucy the morning after she passes out. 
#SaveLockwoodandCo #HauntedWatchParty

Another example of food being a love language is the way that, while we never see Lockwood prepare food for himself, we see George bringing Lockwood's favourite meal- ghormeh sabzi- up to Lockwood's room on a tray with tea! 
#SaveLockwoodandCo #HauntedWatchParty

Lockwood is seen preparing food for Lucy in the show twice; once in the barge cafe, and again in the kitchen. Both times he's preparing toast, which we know from the books is his favourite.

An example of how giving food is a love language!
#SaveLockwoodandCo #HauntedWatchParty

The show adds these little details, too. In Ep1, Lockwood notices how Lucy hasn't eaten, probably in a long time. He exchanges a concerned look with George. 

#SaveLockwoodandCo #HauntedWatchParty

In THB, after Lockwood is badly hurt, when George and Lucy are in the kitchen, George watches Lucy carefully; he asks her if she's eaten. She hasn't. He insists she does, twice.
He watches her the entire scene, looking after her.
#SaveLockwoodandCo #HauntedWatchParty

But the biggest thing about food in this world is the fact that the characters are constantly checking in to ensure they've each eaten. 

To them, food is like a love language.
#SaveLockwoodandCo #HauntedWatchParty

In TCS, there's an entire scene dedicated to Lockwood sitting on the porch of the house, where he eats an entire chocolate bar. 
Chocolate is a huge part of the story; it's passed around constantly during cases to keep their energy up

#SaveLockwoodandCo #HauntedWatchParty

In THB, the end of their case is rewarded with a gigantic chocolate cake!
In TCS, George cooks a great sandwich absolutely loaded with bacon!
Food is treated as something wonderful, something to be enjoyed and celebrated!
#SaveLockwoodandCo #HauntedWatchParty
